bug.description:
Warnings for tensorflow when running keras-bert example from site: <denchmark-link:https://blogs.rstudio.com/tensorflow/posts/2019-09-30-bert-r/>https://blogs.rstudio.com/tensorflow/posts/2019-09-30-bert-r/</denchmark-link>
Warnings for tensorflow while creating keras-bert nodel fromo url. RStudio Version 1.2.1335 R version 3.5.3 tensorflow version 1.14 keras version 2.2.4 latest version of keras_bert code to reproduce issue: #install and test bert-keras #need tensorflow 1.14 or 1.15!!! Sys.setenv(TF_KERAS=1) library(dplyr) library(zeallot) <denchmark-h:h1>make sure we use python 3</denchmark-h>
reticulate::use_python('C:/Users/anawima/AppData/Local/Continuum/anaconda3/python.exe', required=T) <denchmark-h:h1>to see python version</denchmark-h>
reticulate::py_config() reticulate::py_module_available('keras_bert') #check tensorflow and keras versions tensorflow::tf_version() keras:::keras_version() #install.packages("tensorflow") #install.packages("keras") #library("keras") #install_keras() #zip file locatsions pretrained_path = '/Users/anawima/Downloads/uncased_L-12_H-768_A-12/uncased_L-12_H-768_A-12' config_path = file.path(pretrained_path, 'bert_config.json') checkpoint_path = file.path(pretrained_path, 'bert_model.ckpt') vocab_path = file.path(pretrained_path, 'vocab.txt') #impor keras-bert model library(reticulate) k_bert = import('keras_bert') token_dict = k_bert$load_vocabulary(vocab_path) tokenizer = k_bert$Tokenizer(token_dict) #define model parameters and column names seq_length = 50L bch_size = 70 epochs = 1 learning_rate = 1e-4 DATA_COLUMN = 'comment_text' LABEL_COLUMN = 'target' #load model model = k_bert$load_trained_model_from_checkpoint( config_path, checkpoint_path, training=T, trainable=T, seq_len=seq_length) ######################################### console output: WARNING:tensorflow:Entity <bound method TokenEmbedding.call of <keras_bert.layers.embedding.TokenEmbedding object at 0x000001E7DF73E828>> could not be transformed and will be executed as-is.
